Some common blood test parameters include:

* Hemoglobin (Hb): measures the amount of red blood cells in your blood. Normal range is 12-16 g/dL for adults.
* Hematocrit (Hct): measures the percentage of red blood cells in your blood. Normal range is 37-48% for adults.
* Red Blood Cell Count (RBC): measures the number of red blood cells in your blood. Normal range is 4.5-5.5 million cells/mcL for adults.
